title: Firefighters douse Castaic brush fire along 5 Freeway
text: CASTAIC >> A brush fire scorched about 15 acres in the Castaic area Friday afternoon and resulted in the closure of three northbound lanes of the 5 Freeway. The fire was reported about noon near the northbound 5 at Templin Highway. Two SuperScooper airplanes and five helicopters were sent to the scene, the county fire department reported. The fire was put out about 2 p.m., said Nathan Judy of the U.S. Forest Service. There were no reports of damage or injuries. Advertisement
